DOWNLOAD UBUNTU ON WINDOWS (as VS CODE is not easy to work with for this particular program)
set it up
prompt it with command to familiarize with your system and intsall updates if needed ---- command -----> sudo apt update
the last part is only the command 
this is the initial process to set it up and get your stuff dialed in .... need not be done every time
since you have the files ready on your computer
enter the command ----- .\server 
this establishes the server
enter the command ----- .\client
this establishes the client
keep in mind to open two separate applications of ubuntu for a better view(like in the screenshot(1))
the text file of the dns is read by the code and can be manipulated with.... get creative
